<record>
<name>blasting</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>medium</power>
<value>20000</value>
<aura>moderate evocation</aura>
<align>CLNGE</align>
<hint>nil</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>This %Item% appears to be a normal %Item%. But if the command word is spoken and the %Item% is then %Use%, it deals 5d6 points of sonic damage to creatures within a 40-foot cone and causes them to be deafened for 2d6 rounds (a DC 16 Fortitude save reduces the damage by half and negates the deafening). Crystalline objects and creatures take 7d6 points of sonic damage, with no save unless they're held, worn, or carried by creatures (Will DC 16 negates). If a {Cap~%Item%} of Blasting is used magically more than once in a given day, there is a 20 percent cumulative chance with each extra use that it explodes and deals 10d6 points of damage to the person using it.</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
<name>blasting</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>major</power>
<value>70000</value>
<aura>strong evocation</aura>
<align>CLNGE</align>
<hint>nil</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>This %Item% appears to be a normal %Item%. But if the command word is spoken and the %Item% is then %Use%, it deals 10d6 points of sonic damage, stuns creatures for 1 round, and deafens them for 4d6 rounds to creatures within a 40-foot cone (a DC Fortitude reduces the damage by half and negates the stunning and deafening). Crystalline objects and creatures take 16d6 points of sonic damage, with no save unless they're held, worn, or carried by creatures (Will DC 16 negates). If a {Cap~%Item%} of blasting is used magically more than once in a given day, there is a 20 percent cumulative chance with each extra use that it explodes and deals 10d6 points of damage to the person using it.</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
<name>blending</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>major</power>
<value>30000</value>
<aura>moderate illusion</aura>
<align>CLNGE</align>
<hint>nil</hint>
<modify>bonus</modify>
<roll>10</roll>
<bonus>hide</bonus>
<dmdescrip>This magic %Item% enables its user to appear to be part of his surroundings. This allows %GenderObj% a +10 competence bonus on Hide checks. The user can adopt the appearance of another creature, as with the disguise self spell, at will. All creatures acquainted with and friendly to the user see %GenderObj% normally.</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
