<record>
<name>brightness</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>medium</power>
<value>13000</value>
<aura>faint evocation</aura>
<align>CLNG</align>
<hint>nil</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>Upon utterance of a command word, the %Item% emits bright light of one of three sorts.  One command word causes the %Type% to shed light as a hooded lantern. This use of the %Type% does not expend any charges.  Another command word causes The {Cap~%Item%} of Brightness to send out a bright ray 1 foot in diameter and 50 feet long. This strikes as a ranged touch attack, and any creature struck by this beam is blinded for 1d4 rounds unless it makes a DC 14 Fortitude save. This use of the %Type% expends 1 charge.  The third command word causes the %Item% to flare in a blinding flash of light that fills a 30-foot cone. Although this glare lasts but a moment, any creature within the cone must make a DC 14 Fortitude save or be blinded for 1d4 rounds. This use expends 5 charges. The %Item% has up to 50 charges. When all its charges are expended, the %Item% becomes nonmagical.</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
<name>building</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>medium</power>
<value>13000</value>
<aura>faint transmutation</aura>
<align>CLNGE</align>
<hint>craftsman</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>If the proper notes are %Use%, a single use of this %Item% negates any attacks made against all inanimate construction (walls, roof, floor, and so on) within 300 feet. This includes the effects of a horn of blasting, a disintegrate spell, or an attack from a ram or similar siege weapon. The %Item% can be used in this way once per day, with the protection lasting for 30 minutes. The %Item% is also useful with respect to building. Once a week the %Type% can be %Use% so as to produce sounds that magically construct buildings, mines, tunnels, ditches, or whatever. The effect produced in but 30 minutes of playing is equal to the work of 100 humans laboring for three days. Each hour after the first, a character playing the %Item% must make a DC 18 Perform (musical instruments) check. If it fails, %GenderSub% must stop and cannot play the %Item% again for this purpose until a week has passed.</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
<name>chaos</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>major</power>
<value>160000</value>
<aura>strong various</aura>
<align>C</align>
<hint>nil</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>The %Item% grants its possessor the following powers: Confusion, lesser; Magic circle against law; Word of chaos; Cloak of chaos.  Each power is usable 1d4 times per day. This is rolled for each power individually and the character does not know the results. A nonchaotic character who possesses a {Cap~%Item%} of Chaos gains one negative level. Although this level never results in actual level loss, it remains as long as the %Item% is in the character's possession and cannot be overcome in any way (including restoration spells).</dmdescrip>
</record>
