<aura>moderate abjuration</aura>
<align>CLNGE</align>
<hint>shadow</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>This enchanted item protects the owner from scrying and magical location just as a nondetection spell does. If a divination spell is attempted against the owner, the caster of the divination must succeed on a caster level check (1d20 + caster level) against a DC of 19 (as if the caster had cast nondetection on himself ).</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
<name>ogre strength</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>minor</power>
<value>4000</value>
<aura>faint transmutation</aura>
<align>CLNGE</align>
<hint>powerful animal</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>A {Cap~%Item%} of Ogre Strength grants the wearer great strength, adding a +2 enhancement bonus to his Strength score.</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
<name>opening</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>minor</power>
<value>3000</value>
<aura>moderate transmutation</aura>
<align>CLNGE</align>
<hint>nil</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>A {Cap~%Item%} of Opening, when struck, sends forth magical vibrations that cause locks, lids, doors, valves, and portals to open. The device functions against normal bars, shackles, chains, bolts, and so on. A chime of opening also automatically dispels a hold portal spell or even an arcane lock cast by a wizard of lower than 15th level. The %Item% must be within 10 feet of the item or gate to be loosed or opened (which must be visible and known to the user). The %Item% is then struck, a clear tone rings forth, and in 1 round the target lock is unlocked, the shackle is loosed, the secret door is opened, or the lid of the chest is lifted. Each sounding only opens one form of locking, so if a chest is chained, padlocked, locked, and arcane locked, it takes four uses to get it open. A silence spell negates the power of the device. A brand-new {Cap~%Item%} of Opening can be used a total of ten times before it cracks and becomes useless.</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
<name>pain</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>medium</power>
<value>12000</value>
<aura>faint enchantment</aura>
<align>CNE</align>
<hint>nil</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>The {Cap~%Item%} of Pain appears like a normal %Type% with nothing to reveal its true nature. When played by someone who succeeds on a DC 15 Perform (musical instrument) check, the %Item% create a wondrous melody. All within 30 feet must make a DC 14 Will save or be fascinated by the sound. (This is a mind-affecting sonic compulsion.) As soon as the %Item% stops, all those affected are stricken by intense pain at even the slightest noise. Unless a character is in a totally silent area, %GenderSub% takes 1d4 points of damage per round for 2d4 rounds. During this time, damage from sonic attacks is doubled. Thereafter, the least noise causes an affected character to become shaken (except when %GenderSub% is in a totally silent area). This hypersensitivity is a curse and therefore hard to remove (see the bestow curse spell).</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
<name>panic</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>major</power>
<value>30000</value>
<aura>moderate necromancy</aura>
<align>CNE</align>
<hint>evil outsider</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>When a command word is spoken and the {Cap~%Item%} of Panic %Use%, all creatures within 120 feet (with the exception of those within a 20-foot-radius safe zone around the %Item%) are affected as by a fear spell (Will DC 16 partial). The %Item% can be used once per day.</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
<name>persuasion</name>
<probability>1</probability>
