</record>
<record>
<name>planes</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>major</power>
<value>120000</value>
<aura>strong conjuration</aura>
<align>CLNGE</align>
<hint>outsider</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>This enchanted %Item% holds a black circular lens, although any character looking closely at it sees a dark, moving swirl of color. The %Item% allows its user to utilize plane shift. However, this is a difficult item to master. The user must make a DC 15 Intelligence check in order to get the it take %GenderObj% to the plane (and the specific location on that plane) that %GenderSub% wants. If %GenderSub% fails, the enchanted item transports %GenderObj% and all those traveling with %GenderObj% to a random location on that plane (1-60 d100) or to a random plane (61-100 d100).</dmdescrip>
</record>
<record>
<name>arcane</name>
<probability>1</probability>
<power>minor</power>
<value>7400</value>
<aura>moderate abjuration</aura>
<align>CLNGE</align>
<hint>nil</hint>
<modify>nil</modify>
<roll>nil</roll>
<bonus>nil</bonus>
<dmdescrip>This %Item% is a standard book for wizard's spells. All such books are durable and if closed, cannot be harmed by water, acid, fire or electricity. The book is also locked (Arcane Lock) and cannot be opened unless the command word is spoken. A wizard can fill the 1,000 pages of the {Cap~%Item%} of the Arcane as any spell book. This book is never found as randomly generated treasure with spells already inscribed in it.</dmdescrip>
</record>
